summary: An ordinance accepting a deed from Highland Park and Lake Burien Railroad to the City of Seattle, executed January 14, 1914, and other deeds, assignments of certain leases and agreements, and the surrender or assignment of those certain franchises no. 26825 and no. 29101, heretofore granted by said city to W. H. Coughlin, his successors and assigns, and that certain franchise heretofore granted George W. H. White, his successors and assigns, by King County and assigned to the City, and accepting Two Thousand, Two Hundred ($2,200.00) Dollars heretofore deposited with the City of Seattle by said railroad company.
